                    <ab>(C.) In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName ref="#people/124"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Fridericus</persName> dei gratia Romanorum <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> augustus. Quia Romani imperii regimen
                        potestatemque suscepimus, ecclesiis a nostris predecessoribus plurima
                        largitione sublimatis regia nos competit provisione consulere et, ne ipsarum
                        possessiones aliqua distractione depereant, suffragium sufficiens adhibere.
                        Presentibus igitur ac futuris Christi fidelibus volumus esse cognitum, quod
                        petitione domini <rs key="#Popes">pape</rs>
                        <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/409">Eugenii</persName> tertii et
                        intercedente karissimo <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellario</rs> nostro
                            <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Arnaldus cancellarius"
                                >Arnoldo</name></persName> aliisque pluribus regni principibus
                        venerabilem Vercellensem <rs key="#Bishops">episcopum</rs>
                        <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/410">Vgucionem</persName> atque
                        ecclesiam <orgName key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/81">sancti
                            Eusebii </orgName>in regiam protectionem suscepimus et presentis
                        privilegii pagina <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">conmunivimus</rs>.
                        Quecumque ergo memorate ecclesie largitione regum, concessione pontificum
                        seu quorumlibet oblatione fidelium collata esse noscuntur et que in posterum
                        largiente domino conferentur, <rs key="#Castle">castella</rs> sive <rs
                            key="#Villas">villas</rs>, prata, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascua</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Wine">vineas</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers #Lakes #Shores">aquas</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Mills">molendina</rs>, culta et inculta, <rs key="#Districtio"
                            >districtum</rs>, <rs key="#Tolls">pedaticum</rs>, naulum et omnia, que
                        in suis privilegiis a nostris predecessoribus regibus seu imperatoribus sibi
                        concessis contineri noscuntur, presenti privilegio confirmamus, ex quibus
                        hec propriis duximus exprimenda vocabulis: <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/107">sancti Michaelis in
                                <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/328">Laucelio</placeName></orgName> cum suis
                        pertinentiis, monasterium <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/123"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            >sancti Stephani</orgName> cum suis pertinentiis, monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/278">sancti Salvatoris de<placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                                ref="#places/732"> Bessia</placeName></orgName> cum suis
                        pertinentiis, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/734">Tridinum</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/735">Matascum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/230"
                            key="#Islands #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Casale sancti Euasii</placeName> cum omnibus <rs key="#Islands"
                            >insulis</rs> et pertinentiis, <rs key="#Castle">castellum</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/566">sancti Georgii</placeName>, <placeName
                            ref="#places/740"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Ozanum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/741"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
